	"keywords": "100devs, Learn To Code, Podcast",
	"description": "On this week&#x27;s episode of the podcast, I interview Leon Noel, founder of 100Devs\nand head of engineering at Resilient Coders.\n\nGrowing up, Leon had it drilled into him that he had to become a doctor, lawyer,\nor dentist. But his ambitions grew and he went on to have an exciting career in\ntech.\n\nAfter a successful exit from a startup, Leon wanted to help folks who were\nstruggling during the pandemic. He started 100Devs, a charity which has helped\n10,000s of people learn to code.\n\nWe talk about:\n\n ",
	"headline": "Leon Noel has Helped THOUSANDS of People Learn to Code [100Devs founder on freeCodeCamp Podcast #117]",
