	"description": "\n\nThis week I interview Phoebe Voong-Fadel about her childhood as the daughter of\nrefugees, and how she self-studied coding and became a professional developer at\nthe age of 36.\n\nPhoebe worked from age 12 at her parent&#x27;s Chinese take-out restaurant. She was\nable to study history at the London School of Economics, before working in\nhigher ed.\n\nShe left her job to raise two kids due to the high cost of childcare in the UK.\nAfter two years of teaching herself to code using freeCodeCamp, she got her",
